PARIS (AP) — Marseille missed the chance to move three points clear in second place in the French league after conceding a last-minute equalizer in a 1-1 draw at struggling Troyes on Sunday.Striker Yoann Touzghar profited from poor Marseille defending to slide in the equalizer after playmaker Dimitri Payet’s penalty put Marseille ahead in the 28th minute. It was Payet’s club-leading ninth league goal of the season.Second place guarantees entry into next season’s Champions League, and Marseille is one point of Nice in third place and a playoff spot.Later Sunday, Lyon hosted defending champion Lille.OTHER MATCHESNorthern side Lens moved into sixth place in the chase for the European places after a 2-1 win at Angers, with Jonathan Clauss hitting a floating shot that lobbed goalkeeper Danijel Petkovic in the 77th.Lens is three points behind fourth-place Rennes in the Europa League spot.ADVERTISEMENTMonaco lost 2-1 at home to Reims, despite striker Wissam Ben Yedder’s league-leading 15th goal to move one ahead of Paris Saint-Germain star Kylian Mbappe.SportsPoland rejects FIFA ruling Russia can play qualifier as RFUUkraine athletes defend country, demand sanctions for RussiaMcLaughlin wins 1st IndyCar race in St. Pete season openerMLB players, teams talk for 7th day in row, deadline nearsThe visitors equalized in the 84th when Monaco striker Kevin Volland headed an own-goal and, soon after Monaco midfielder Jean Lucas was sent off, scored a stoppage-time winner through striker Nathanael Mbuku. Lorient moved out of the relegation zone with a 1-0 win at Brest as fellow strugglers Bordeaux and Metz both drew.Last-place Bordeaux drew 1-1 at Clermont and 18th-place Metz was held 0-0 at home by Nantes.PSG beat Saint-Etienne 3-1 on Saturday after falling behind for the 13th time in 26 games and travels to Nice next Saturday.___More AP soccer: https://apnews.com/hub/soccer and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports